{"nodes": [{"id": "2026_05_29_todos_search_functionality_design_document", "label": "Design", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-29-todos-search-functionality/design.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_05_29_todos_search_functionality_design_context", "label": "Context", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-29-todos-search-functionality/design.md", "source_location": "line 1", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "The Vim extension owns modal prompt editing through `src/modal/*`, command parsing in `src/commands.ts`, buffer transforms in `src/buffer.ts`, and Pi adapter effects in `src/vim-editor.ts`. `TODOS.md` still lists `/` search as unsupported. Insert-mode slash behavior must remain delegated to Pi so Pi slash-command completion keeps working; this change only handles `/` while Vim normal/visual/operator-pending mode is active. Search needs small cross-module state: active search input while collecti"}, {"id": "2026_05_29_todos_search_functionality_design_goals_non_goals", "label": "Goals / Non-Goals", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-29-todos-search-functionality/design.md", "source_location": "line 7", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "**Goals:** - Support normal-mode `/` query entry and forward search across the current prompt buffer."}, {"id": "2026_05_29_todos_search_functionality_design_decisions", "label": "Decisions", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-29-todos-search-functionality/design.md", "source_location": "line 25", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "1. **Represent search as modal state, not Pi prompt text.** - Add `pendingSearch` state for query collection and `lastSearch` state for repeat navigation. - Rationale: normal-mode `/` is command input, not literal prompt insertion. Keeping it in modal state avoids corrupting prompt text."}, {"id": "2026_05_29_todos_search_functionality_design_risks_trade_offs", "label": "Risks / Trade-offs", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-29-todos-search-functionality/design.md", "source_location": "line 50", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "- Search query collection may conflict with existing pending operator/register/mark state \u2192 Only enter search from modes where `/` is valid; `Esc` cancels and clears pending search. - Search across multi-line prompt can produce off-by-one cursor bugs \u2192 Keep matching in buffer helpers with unit tests for line boundaries, wrap-around, and no-match cases. - Operator-pending search ranges may differ from exact Vim edge cases \u2192 Define tested prompt-local behavior and keep unsupported offsets out of s"}, {"id": "2026_05_29_todos_search_functionality_design_migration_plan", "label": "Migration Plan", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-29-todos-search-functionality/design.md", "source_location": "line 58", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "1. Add search state/types and command parsing for `/`, `n`, and `N`. 2. Add pure buffer search helpers and range helpers with tests. 3. Wire normal-mode search query collection, cancellation, completion, and repeat navigation."}, {"id": "2026_05_29_todos_search_functionality_design_open_questions", "label": "Open Questions", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-29-todos-search-functionality/design.md", "source_location": "line 70", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "None. v1 uses literal, prompt-local, wrap-around search. `/` starts forward search; `n` repeats last direction; `N` inverts it. `?` backward search remains out of scope."}, {"id": "2026_05_29_todos_search_functionality_design_ref_src_commands_ts", "label": "commands.ts", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-29-todos-search-functionality/design.md", "source_location": "line 3", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_05_29_todos_search_functionality_design_ref_src_buffer_ts", "label": "buffer.ts", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-29-todos-search-functionality/design.md", "source_location": "line 3", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_05_29_todos_search_functionality_design_ref_src_vim_editor_ts", "label": "vim-editor.ts", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-29-todos-search-functionality/design.md", "source_location": "line 3", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}], "edges": [{"source": "2026_05_29_todos_search_functionality_design_document", "target": "2026_05_29_todos_search_functionality_design_context", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-29-todos-search-functionality/design.md", "source_location": "line 1", "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "2026_05_29_todos_search_functionality_design_document", "target": "2026_05_29_todos_search_functionality_design_goals_non_goals", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-29-todos-search-functionality/design.md", "source_location": "line 7", "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "2026_05_29_todos_search_functionality_design_document", "target": "2026_05_29_todos_search_functionality_design_decisions", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRA